'''Saku Shrine''' (佐久神社) is a Japanese shrine. Several shrines with the same name are located primarily in Shizuoka Prefecture and Yamanashi Prefecture.
* {{ill|Saku Shrine (Kofu)|ja|佐久神社 (甲府市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - A shrine located in Kofu City, Yamanashi Prefecture. Relocated by the feudal lord Kōzan Izumo no Kami in the 13th year of Tenbun (1543). * {{ill|Saku Shrine (Fuefuki)|ja|佐久神社 (笛吹市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - A shrine located in Fuefuki City, Yamanashi Prefecture. * {{ill|Saku Shrine (Shizuoka)|ja|佐久神社 (静岡市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - A shrine located in Shimizu Ward, Shizuoka City, Shizuoka Prefecture. == See Also == * {{ill|Sakunado Shrine|ja|佐久奈度神社|12=draft|12=draft}} - A shrine located in Ōtsu City, Shiga Prefecture. * {{ill|Ihasaku Shrine|ja|伊波佐久神社|12=draft|12=draft}} - A shrine located in Toyama City, Toyama Prefecture.
{{Aimai}} [[simple:user:immanuelle/佐久神社]]
